---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="About" description="What I do when I'm not building APIs and data pipelines.">
  <header class="section-head">
    <h1>When I'm Not Coding</h1>
  </header>

  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="about-card">
      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="about-icon">⚽</div>
        <h2>Football</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-content">
        <p>
          I play pickup and league soccer at Astoria Park in Queens. There's something about the
          flow of the game that clears my head after a day of debugging distributed systems.
        </p>
        <p>
          Been following Premier League for years, mainly Liverpool. Watching Salah's runs or 
          rewatching Messi's prime Barça days never gets old. Neymar's creativity at PSG and 
          Santos was unmatched—still one of my favorites to watch.
        </p>
        <p>
          The tactical side of football reminds me of system design: positioning, spacing, 
          anticipating moves several steps ahead. Both require reading patterns and adapting quickly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-card">
      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="about-icon">🎮</div>
        <h2>Gaming</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-content">
        <p>
          RPGs and first-person shooters on Xbox. <strong>GTA San Andreas</strong> is still my 
          all-time favorite—the open world, the story, the freedom to just mess around in Los Santos.
        </p>
        <p>
          These days I'm mostly on <strong>Rainbow Six Siege</strong> when I want tactical 
          gameplay, and <strong>Expedition 33</strong> when I'm in the mood for exploration and lore.
        </p>
        <p>
          Gaming taught me a lot about problem-solving under pressure, adapting strategies on the fly, 
          and the importance of good team coordination—skills that translate surprisingly well to 
          incident response and production debugging.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-card">
      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="about-icon">🇪🇹</div>
        <h2>Roots & Culture</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-content">
        <p>
          Born and raised in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. Moved to the US for university and ended up 
          settling in Queens, NY—one of the most diverse places in the world.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm constantly exploring the city's food scene: Ethiopian spots in Little Ethiopia, 
          Pakistani food in Jackson Heights, Korean BBQ in Flushing. Every neighborhood has its 
          own character and story.
        </p>
        <p>
          Queens feels like home because of that mix—everyone's from somewhere else, everyone's 
          got their own background, but we're all navigating the same subway delays and bodega runs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-card">
      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="about-icon">λ</div>
        <h2>Functional Programming</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-content">
        <p>
          Outside of work, I'm diving deeper into functional programming with Scala. Currently 
          building a chess engine as a learning project—implementing move generation, game state 
          validation, and search algorithms using purely functional principles.
        </p>
        <p>
          Working through the <em>Functional Programming in Scala</em> (Red Book) exercises to 
          sharpen my understanding of functional abstractions, type classes, and effect systems.
        </p>
        <p>
          What draws me to FP is the way it makes complex state management simpler through 
          immutability, and how it encourages thinking about composition and abstraction in a 
          more mathematical way. It's a different mindset from the imperative code I write at work, 
          but the patterns and discipline carry over.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .about-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .about-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .about-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-icon {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3));
  }

  .about-header h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .about-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .about-content p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .about-content strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about-content em {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .about-icon {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .about-header h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
